<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1944,2036]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,536]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,2012,2036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is from the combination of 
<emphasis box="[872,952,2013,2036]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">macro-</emphasis>
(long, large) and 
<emphasis box="[1151,1221,2013,2036]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">cornis</emphasis>
(horned), referring to the large spur on the front surface of the male chelicera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,187,212]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from other species by the presence of a large spur on the front surface of the male chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,407,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,407,1923]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 70. Ilargus macrocornis sp. nov. 67 male holotype, dorsal view; 68 male left palp, ventral view; 69 male left palp, retrolateral view; 70 male left chelicera, internal view. Scale bars: 67, 1.0 mm; 68 – 70, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209895/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,244,223,247]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="70.0">70</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,259,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,409,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[422,524,260,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00152). Carapace length 
<number box="[985,1023,260,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.7">1.7</number>
; abdomen length 
<number box="[1219,1257,260,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1.7">1.7</number>
. Chelicera (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,407,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,407,1923]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 70. Ilargus macrocornis sp. nov. 67 male holotype, dorsal view; 68 male left palp, ventral view; 69 male left palp, retrolateral view; 70 male left chelicera, internal view. Scale bars: 67, 1.0 mm; 68 – 70, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209895/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,184,295,319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="70.0">70</number>
</figureCitation>
): red brown; front surface with a long curved spur proximally. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[980,1114,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,407,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,407,1923]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 70. Ilargus macrocornis sp. nov. 67 male holotype, dorsal view; 68 male left palp, ventral view; 69 male left palp, retrolateral view; 70 male left chelicera, internal view. Scale bars: 67, 1.0 mm; 68 – 70, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209895/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Figs 
<number box="[1039,1114,295,319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="68.5" valueMax="69.0" valueMin="68.0">68–69</number>
</figureCitation>
): tibia and cymbium yellow brown, other segments cream. Embolus long and coiled for less a circle, with a short and thin lamella; proximal tegular lobe large; retrolateral tibial apophysis finger-like; ventral tibial bump absent. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[1394,1432,367,391]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.2">4.2</number>
, II 
<number box="[177,215,404,428]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2.9">2.9</number>
, III 
<number box="[262,299,404,428]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.3">3.3</number>
, IV 
<number box="[349,387,404,428]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.8">3.8</number>
. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[598,683,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 70" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,407,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,407,1923]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 70. Ilargus macrocornis sp. nov. 67 male holotype, dorsal view; 68 male left palp, ventral view; 69 male left palp, retrolateral view; 70 male left chelicera, internal view. Scale bars: 67, 1.0 mm; 68 – 70, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209895/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Fig. 
<number box="[651,683,404,428]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="67.0">67</number>
</figureCitation>
): carapace dark brown, eye area with guanine deposits, behind eye area with a medial and two marginal yellowish stripes; abdomen dark brown, with many silvery white speckles and a large leaf-like marking medially; legs yellowish to dark brown.
</paragraph>
